
pvm_tidtohost(1)               Scilab function               pvm_tidtohost(1)
NAME
  pvm_tidtohost - returns the host of the specified PVM process.

CALLING SEQUENCE
  [dtid] = pvm_tidtohost(tid)

PARAMETERS

  tid  : integer, task identifier of the PVM process in question.

  dtid
      : integer, the tid of the host's pvmd3 or a negative value if an error.

DESCRIPTION

  pvm_tidtohost returns the host id on which the process identified by tid is
  located.
EXAMPLE
  dtid = pvm_tidtohost(pvm_mytid())

SEE ALSO
  pvm_config, pvm_tasks
